## LEMON PEA SMASH

**INGREDIENTS**

* 2 c. fresh shelled peas (thawed & drained if from frozen)
* 1 clove garlic, peeled & smashed
* 1/4 c. fresh flat leaf parseley
* 2 - 3 tbsp olive oil
* 1 TBSP finely chopped salted preserved lemon peel
* 2 TBSP finely chopped chive or scallion
* 1 TBSP lemon juice or red wine vinegar
* 1/4 tsp hot cayenne pepper or red pepper flakes (optional, to taste)
* salt, to taste
* black pepper, to taste


**PREPARATION**

1. In a food processor, blend the peas, garlic, parseley and olive oil together until your desired consistency is reached.  Chunky vs Smooth is a personal preference.
2. Scoop the ingredients into a small bowl.  Mixing by hand, add the lemon peel, scallion, vinegar/lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
